CNCP v1 23199
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#9908: Template ref array is updated twice when an array ref dependency is changed",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:17.631906+00:00",
  "text": "Template ref array is updated twice when an array ref dependency is changed\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nPlease observe the output from the computed property `c`.\n\n### What is expected?\n\n`elements` should only update once when `numbers` is updated.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n`elements` is first set to `[]` before it is populated, causing any dependent computed properties to be evaluated twice.\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nPerhaps this behaviour is intentional? :thinking:",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
